    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-22T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-22T11:00:00-05:00" n="160"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d160">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/1302: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-22T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 22, 1939—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:21 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>165. Department’s telegram No. 124, December 21, 6 p.m. Panamanian Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs cordially approves procedure suggested and the President of
                    Panama will transmit statement to the three belligerents tomorrow December 23, 5
                        p.m.<note n="38" xml:id="d160fn38">The statement was released by the
                        Department of State on December 23; for text, see Department of State <hi
                            rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, December 23, 1939, p. 723.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
